00:09:24.572 --> 00:09:27.200
This is a cool way
of illustrating a concept

00:09:27.200 --> 00:09:29.100
that when you're in a boat,
and you're in the ocean,

00:09:29.100 --> 00:09:30.700
if you ever see water that's bubbling,

00:09:30.700 --> 00:09:32.000
you're supposed to avoid it.

00:09:32.300 --> 00:09:35.000
A boat floats on the water
because the boat plus the air

00:09:35.000 --> 00:09:38.400
in it has a lower average density
than the water underneath it.

00:09:38.600 --> 00:09:42.500
However, water with are bubbling up
through it has a lower average density

00:09:42.500 --> 00:09:43.400
than regular water,

00:09:43.400 --> 00:09:44.740
and you can hit a critical point,

00:09:44.740 --> 00:09:46.600
where your boat,
even with nothing wrong with it,

00:09:46.600 --> 00:09:49.300
can just sink right down
into the water air mixture.

00:09:49.820 --> 00:09:53.080
If you think of this sand
as water and the air as air,

00:09:53.340 --> 00:09:55.140
you can get something similar happening.

00:09:55.140 --> 00:09:58.500
These pieces of plastic,
they float on top of the sand.

00:09:58.700 --> 00:10:02.600
However, once there's air floating
through the density of the sand goes down

00:10:02.600 --> 00:10:04.460
and these pieces of plastic,

00:10:05.520 --> 00:10:07.360
